- DELETE: Acceptable (there is a DELETE mapping: /consumer/{username}/notifications to deleteAllNotifications).

- PATCH: Not acceptable (no PATCH mapping for this path).

The ConsumerController defines two handlers for /consumer/{username}/notifications: one for DELETE (deleteAllNotifications) and one for PUT (readAllNotifications). There are no handlers for GET, POST, PATCH, OPTIONS, HEAD, TRACE, or other methods on this path. Therefore only PUT and DELETE are supported by the code, while all other methods are not. HEAD is not considered acceptable since there is no GET handler to base a HEAD response on, and the code does not provide an explicit HEAD mapping. OPTIONS is also not explicitly supported by mappings in the code.
